Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:54.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{A-A snake! - OG}I-It's a snake!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.72,0:01:55.80,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Is this...? - OG}Could this be...?{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.18,0:01:58.43,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kalgara! Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.06,0:02:04.02,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What a shock! I didn't know that snake had a grandchild... - OG}What a surprise! That snake\Nmust have had a grandchild.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:06.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,"That snake"?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.52,0:02:09.61,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{A snake, huh? - OG}Snake, huh?{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.86,0:02:16.95,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Those two make no sense... - OG}I don't get those two...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.95,0:02:20.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,They were trying to kill each other\Nuntil just recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.04,0:02:22.54,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Now, they're such good friends! - OG}but now, they're\Npractically inseparable!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.54,0:02:26.25,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Kalgara is never very friendly with any of the villagers, either. - OG}Kalgara's not even that friendly\Nwith his fellow villagers.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.25,0:02:29.75,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I've never seen him smile like that before... - OG}I've never seen him smile\Nlike this before...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.96,0:02:33.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Just follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.13,0:02:36.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We climb down here. - OG}We'll climb down through here.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.97,0:02:38.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Climb down?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.69,0:02:51.53,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,This ringing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.53,0:02:55.78,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kalgara! Where is this\Nbeautiful ringing coming from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:02:58.74,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Follow me and you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.45,0:03:38.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.03,0:03:40.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Lost for words?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:41.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This is Shandia, a city of gold. - OG}This is Shandora, the City of Gold.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.87,0:03:44.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We are its survivors! - OG}We are what remains of its people.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:47.37,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,A city of gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:50.88,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's like I'm dreaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:54.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{W-Whoa! It's gold everywhere! - OG}Wh-Whoa! It's all gold!{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:58.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's a city of treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:04:01.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hey, guys! Stop! - OG}H-Hey, guys! Come on!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:03.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:08.10,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Load your ship with all the treasure\Nyou can, aside from the gold bell! - OG}Load your ship with all the treasure\Nyou want, aside from the golden bell!{Polly/Z}{Leave the golden bell. Otherwise,\Ntake as much as your ship can carry! - CB}
Comment: 0,0:04:03.22,0:04:05.93,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Load your ship with all the treasure you can, aside from the gold bell!
Comment: 0,0:04:05.93,0:04:08.10,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Load your ship with all the treasure you can, aside from the gold bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.02,0:04:12.65,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The villagers already agreed to it. - OG}We villagers won't\Ntake no for an answer.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:16.86,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We owe you for saving our tribe\Nfrom that terrible disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:18.61,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This is nothing at all. - OG}It's the least we can do.{Nikki/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.36,0:04:21.24,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,You're so generous, Great Warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.24,0:04:26.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,But haven't your people been\Nprotecting the city all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:27.58,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Yes. - OG}Indeed.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.58,0:04:31.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We've protected the city, but... - OG}We've been protecting the city, but...{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.38,0:04:35.21,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{not necessarily its treasure! - OG}{not necessarily because of the gold! - Nikki/Z}to us, the gold holds little value!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.67,0:04:38.09,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,To be more specific...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.52,0:04:47.52,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{only this stone. - OG}we were protecting this stone.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.23,0:04:51.90,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:53.31,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:54.94,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Writings of history. - OG}A historical record.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,It's known as a poneglyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:05:00.07,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We can't read it, either. - OG}Even we are unable to read it.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:04.24,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You mean your ancestors\Ndidn't write this? - OG}You mean this wasn't written\Nby your ancestors?{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.74,0:05:06.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{All we know for certain... - OG}We know one thing for certain:{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.87,0:05:12.83,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{is that this city of Shandora fought and fell trying to protect this stone. - OG}Shandora fell during a desperate\Nbattle to protect this stone.{Z}{Shandora fell to ruin\Nfighting to protect this stone. - CB/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.17,0:05:17.42,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We must continue to protect it\Nwith that amount of resolve. - OG}We must continue to protect it\Nwith the same resolve.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{As descendants - OG}As their descendants,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.01,0:05:23.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{it is our duty to protect\Nthe proof that our ancestors fought and survived. - OG}we must protect the legacy for which\Nour ancestors risked their lives.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.80,0:05:27.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We revere our ancestors\Nas if they were gods. - OG}We revere our forefathers\Nas we would gods.{PP/Z}{We honor our forefathers\Nas we would gods. - Nikki/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.81,0:05:33.86,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Still, I had no idea it was\Nthis giant, gold bell I had heard... - OG}{\q2}Who would've thought it was the ringing\Nof such a massive golden bell...{\q2}{PP/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This bell's ringing has words to it. - OG}That ringing carries a message.{CB/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.69,0:05:40.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Words? - OG}A message?{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:44.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So that the spirits of our ancestors who were greeted by the heavens - OG}It's for our ancestors who\Nwere greeted by the heavens.{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:49.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{can return to this land at any time without getting lost, - OG}So that they may always be guided\Nback home to this land,{Polly/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.12,0:05:52.67,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{we continue to ring this bell, as a way to say, - OG}we continue to ring this bell,\Nas a way to say:{Polly/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:56.09,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,"We are here."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.21,0:06:02.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Its sound proclaims the unquestionable glory Shandia once had, - OG}Its sound proclaims the undeniable\Nglory of Shandora's past,{CB/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:06.10,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,and makes its existence known\Nto the ends of the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.10,0:06:09.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We will never run or hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.10,0:06:14.94,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,That is why we call this city's\Ngrand bell the "Light of Shandora."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.48,0:06:18.98,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{That explains why it has such a majestic sound! - OG}A fitting name to match\Nits majestic sound.{Z/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:20.36,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Do you think so?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:21.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.03,0:06:26.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This light reached out to us and helped us arrive here. - OG}{The light reached out and guided us\Nthrough the storm to get here. - CB}That day, the light embraced us\Nand guided us here.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:35.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I heard this bell in a storm where it shouldn't have been audible... - OG}{It should have been inaudible through\Nthe storm. Yet, I heard this bell. - PP}In the middle of a deafening storm,\NI heard the ringing of this very bell.{Nikki}
Comment: 0,0:06:28.49,0:06:31.70,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,851)}I heard this bell in a storm where it shouldn't have been audible...
Comment: 0,0:06:32.00,0:06:35.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I heard this bell in a storm where it shouldn't have been audible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:43.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You like this bell's sound, too? - OG}You like the sound\Nof this bell too, huh?{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.34,0:06:47.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Are you going to grow up to be like that other giant snake someday? - OG}I wonder if you'll become\Na giant serpent too someday.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.81,0:06:55.73,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Probably not for a hundred more years! - OG}Let's check back\Nin a hundred years or so!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:07:01.48,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stay here as long\Nas you like, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.98,0:07:07.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You're the first guests here in the 400 years since Shandia fell! - OG}Shandora has had no guests\Nsince its fall 400 years ago!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.62,0:07:09.70,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I want to treat you with lavish hospitality! - OG}Let me show you\Nour finest hospitality!{CB/Nikki/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.33,0:07:13.08,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'd love that! - OG}I appreciate it.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:15.83,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I do want to collect plants\Nfrom the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:18.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{and I want to see this plague\Nall the way through. - OG}and I'd like to see this plague\Nthrough to its end.{CB/Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:22.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore! Commodore!
Comment: 0,0:07:18.92,0:07:20.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore!
Comment: 0,0:07:20.38,0:07:22.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:24.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hold on, now. What's with the clothes? - OG}Whoa now, what's with those outfits?{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.05,0:07:26.09,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Look, look! An eternal pose!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:27.84,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,And a map, Commodore! A map!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:32.06,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We took these from intruders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.60,0:07:33.85,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.85,0:07:36.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{This skull shape is definitely this island. - OG}The skull shape is\Ndefinitely this island.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:41.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,The name "Shandora" means\N"the skull's right eye,"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:45.49,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{[/fad(0,1985)]which refers to this city's location. - OG}which points to this city's location.{Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:48.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Well, take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:51.58,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Be sure she gets lots of rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.58,0:07:53.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:58.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come look, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.29,0:08:01.54,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Noland's giving us some weird crops! - OG}Noland said he'll give us\Nsome weird crops!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.54,0:08:06.59,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I have a greenhouse on our ship,\Nwith all kinds of plant samples. - OG}There's a greenhouse on the ship\Nwith all sorts of plant specimens.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:09.84,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll leave some seeds and sprouts that are suited for your soil. - OG}I'll leave some seeds and sprouts\Nthat are suited for your soil.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.84,0:08:11.85,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Is that any good? - OG}Does it taste good?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:14.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Sure is! It's also full of nutrients! - OG}Sure does! {\i1}And{\i0} it's rich in nutrients!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:16.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.99,0:09:18.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Let's work hard again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.29,0:09:21.33,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Work hard doing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.33,0:09:22.96,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Having a campfire party?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.30,0:09:32.64,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.64,0:09:35.35,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Why would the doctor and the others do this?! - OG}Why would the doctor\Nand his friends do this?!{CB/Nikki/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.06,0:09:43.02,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Chief! Noland and\Nthe others are coming! - OG}Chief! Noland's crew is coming!{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:47.65,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Listen! Do not speak of last night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:50.74,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{They said they are going\Nto set sail in a few days. - OG}They said they're planning\Nto set sail in a few days.{Polly/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.11,0:09:55.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do not do anything rash! - OG}Make absolutely sure\Nnot to do anything rash!{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.41,0:09:59.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I guess we can't understand each other after all! - OG}I knew it... Our peoples can\Nnever see eye to eye!{CB/Viz}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.70,0:10:04.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,No matter how good his\Nmedicine is, he's still a godkiller!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.38,0:10:08.80,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do they think they're great enough to stomp all over our history?! - OG}{\q2}Do they think themselves so great\Nthat they can trample all over our history?!{CB/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.59,0:10:14.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Suppress your feelings\Nand quietly wait for them to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.18,0:10:15.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:19.97,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:21.43,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Is Kalgara around?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.32,0:10:34.49,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Why is everyone acting so coldly\Nall of a sudden? Where's Kalgara? - OG}What's with the cold shoulder\Nall of a sudden? Where's Kalgara?{Z/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.49,0:10:37.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{You guys are outsiders! - OG}You guys are still outsiders!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:41.37,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Kalgara doesn't want\Nto see you anymore! - OG}Kalgara said he doesn't want\Nto see you anymore!{CB/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:42.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Seto!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.12,0:10:48.42,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{When are you gonna leave, anyway?! - OG}Just when are you all\Ngoing to leave, anyway?{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.79,0:10:49.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Eh?! - OG}Huh?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:55.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{They suddenly seem to hate us now... - OG}They seem to hate us\Nall of a sudden...{CB}{Out of the blue, they seem\Nto hate us now... - CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.22,0:10:59.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Hey, hold on, you guys! You can't just start acting like this! - OG}Hey, what gives?! The way you're\Nacting doesn't make sense!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.47,0:11:00.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.68,0:11:05.64,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{[/fad(0,1476)]Let's continue our work. - OG}{\fad(0,1476)}Let's just keep working.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.35,0:11:09.06,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We still have some forest to inspect. - OG}We're not done inspecting the forest.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.11,0:11:14.15,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Here you are, Kalgara! - OG}There you are, Kalgara!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:15.86,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Noland was looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:19.41,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. I don't want to see his face anymore. - OG}Yeah. I don't want\Nto see his face again.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:24.50,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If I do, I think I might kill him! - OG}If I do, I might just kill him!{CB}{If I do, I might do\Nsomething I'll regret! - CB/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.88,0:11:33.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,The bell didn't ring today...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:34.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.26,0:11:38.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It's the first time this's happened in the month we've been here. - OG}That hasn't happened in the month\Nwe've been here, has it?{CB/Z/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:40.30,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:43.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll be finished exploring the forest in two days. - OG}We'll be finished inspecting\Nthe forest in two days.{PP/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.47,0:11:44.93,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.56,0:11:50.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Tell the crew we set sail\Nagain in three days,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.44,0:11:54.15,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{so now's their last chance to enjoy solid ground for a while. - OG}so make sure to enjoy\Nthe solid ground while we can.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:11:59.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Commodore... To be honest, I wanna get off this awkward island... - OG}{[/q2]Commodore... if we're no longer welcome\Nhere, why don't we just leave? - CB}Commodore, to be honest, it doesn't\Nfeel right to stay here any longer...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.11,0:12:01.53,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Only after we've finished our duties! - OG}We have to finish what we started!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:02.53,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Get some sleep. - OG}Rest up.{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.91,0:12:07.04,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Live here, Noland! - OG}Stay here, Noland!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.04,0:12:11.04,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{I know! Why don't you make Mousse your wife?! - OG}Oh! Why not take\NMousse as your wife?{Z}{concatenated after "I know!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:12.21,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly!{OG}{Thanks, but no! - Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:15.42,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{I have a family back home, with kids about her age. - OG}I have a family back home,\Nincluding a child about her age.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.42,0:12:16.55,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,I have to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:20.39,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Kalgara doesn't want\Nto see you anymore! - OG}Kalgara said he doesn't want\Nto see you anymore!{CB/Nikki}{10:37}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:25.14,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{When are you gonna leave, anyway?! - OG}Just when are you all\Ngoing to leave, anyway?{CB}{10:45}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.81,0:12:33.07,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I know you're here, Kalgara!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.07,0:12:34.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Come out! - OG}Show yourself!{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:38.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Don't you think this is too one-sided?! - OG}Don't you think I'm owed\Nan explanation?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:39.82,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Tell me why! - OG}Out with it!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:41.78,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I won't understand unless you tell me! - OG}I'm not a mind reader!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.41,0:12:45.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We're going to set sail very soon! - OG}We're setting sail soon!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:47.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I don't want to part ways like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.76,0:13:04.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Don't show your face around me! - OG}Don't show your face\Naround me again!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.18,0:13:07.47,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do you want your wife\Nto end up a widow?! - OG}Or must we part ways\Nthrough death?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.19,0:13:12.65,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Kalgara!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:19.61,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The commodore seems sad... - OG}The commodore seems lonely...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:20.90,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.90,0:13:26.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Just after he made such a great friend all the way out here... - OG}And after making such a great friend\Nso very far from home...{CB/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:30.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,None of this makes any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.16,0:13:34.17,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We set sail first thing\Ntomorrow morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.17,0:13:37.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But the villagers are so bloodthirsty\Nwe can't go near 'em, - OG}The villagers are so bloodthirsty\Nwe can't go near 'em.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.05,0:13:41.13,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{not to mention, the bell didn't ring again today... - OG}Not to mention, the bell\Ndidn't ring today, either...{CB/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.89,0:13:46.93,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Don't show your face around me! - OG}Don't show your face\Naround me again!{CB}{13:00}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:49.89,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Do you want your wife\Nto end up a widow?! - 13:04}Or must we part ways\Nthrough death?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:11.00,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What a heartrending way to leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:11.96,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.54,0:14:17.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.17,0:14:19.67,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Mousse{-chan}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:22.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.93,0:14:30.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Botanist, my ass! - OG}What kind of botanist would do this?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.15,0:14:37.77,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.19,0:14:42.15,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If these are the victims of your "advancements," - OG}If these are the victims\Nof your so-called "progress,"{CB/Polly/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:46.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,then we should never\Nhave accepted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.91,0:14:51.29,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Kindred trees? - OG}Ancestral trees?{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:53.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.33,0:14:58.63,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{It is said that all the spirits of our ancestors who died on this island - OG}It's said that the spirits of our\Nancestors who died on this island{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.63,0:15:02.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{are guided to them by the bell so they can settle inside them. - OG}dwell within them, guided there\Nby the sound of the bell.{CB/Viz}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.34,0:15:06.72,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{All of our ancestors who lived on\Nthe island since the age of Shandora - OG}Our ancestors have lived here\Nsince the age of Shandora long ago.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.72,0:15:13.68,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{watch over us from those sacred, white trees. - OG}{watch over us from\Nthose holy white trees. - CB}Each one of them watches over us\Nfrom those sacred white trees.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.15,0:15:24.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The Kindred Woods are so truly important to us Shandians - OG}To us Shandians,\Nthe ancestral trees are so precious{CB/Polly/Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:31.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{that we've protected them as much as we've protected our own lives! - OG}that we've protected them\Nas we would our own lives!{CB/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.87,0:15:34.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And we chopped them all down... - OG}And we went and\Nchopped them all down...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.25,0:15:40.96,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The warriors were angry and instantly took up their weapons... - OG}{The warriors were\Nimmediately up in arms... - CB}The warriors were so angry\Nthey were immediately up in arms...{Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:43.09,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{We must drive them off this island! - OG}Drive them from the island!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.09,0:15:44.42,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,– Yeah!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.76,0:15:53.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{but since you had saved so many of the villagers' lives... - OG}...but we owed you for saving\Nso many villagers' lives...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.14,0:15:55.02,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:59.10,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So that attitude was anger\Nthey couldn't act on... - OG}{So that attitude was from\Ntheir pent-up anger... - PP}So they were just\Nholding back their anger...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:02.57,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Even if it was just for tree research... - OG}Even if it was for your research...{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.32,0:16:04.78,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,even if you didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.49,0:16:09.11,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{The villagers' anger won't go away now... - OG}the village's anger will never subside.{CB/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:12.28,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So, I thought I would\Nat least ask why... - OG}So, I thought I would at least\Nask before you left...{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.50,0:16:16.71,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{before you left... - OG}Why did you do it?{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:20.58,Secondary-207-,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hey! Someone help with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.58,0:16:21.96,Secondary-207-,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Get it all on board now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:24.55,Secondary-207-,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Make sure to tie them up properly!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.96,0:16:23.17,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Trees where ancestors' spirits dwell... - OG}Trees where the spirits\Nof their ancestors dwell...{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:25.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:28.18,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We've done something that can never be taken back... - OG}We can never take back\Nwhat we've done here.{CB}{We can never make up\Nfor what we've done. - PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:31.01,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,The villagers are right to be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:32.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,But, Commodore!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.14,0:16:33.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,We had no choice, given–
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.22,0:16:35.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{No excuses! - OG}There's no excusing it!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:38.98,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I only did what satisfied me! - OG}{I did what I thought was right... - PP/Viz}I only cared to satisfy\Nmy own conscience...{PP/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.56,0:16:41.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm told... - OG}I was told...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.69,0:16:44.94,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,that aside from proclaiming\Nthe city's existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.94,0:16:49.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{that bell also served to guide their\Nancestors' spirits to the island. - OG}{\q2}that bell also served to guide the\Nspirits of their ancestors back to the island.{Polly/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:54.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And we cut down those trees! - OG}And we cut down the very\Ntrees that housed them!{CB}
Comment: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:52.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,And we cut down those trees!
Comment: 0,0:16:52.66,0:16:54.62,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,And we cut down those trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.12,0:16:57.04,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We have no reason to be forgiven! - OG}They have no reason to forgive us!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:17:00.08,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.46,0:17:04.42,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Listen up, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.42,0:17:06.26,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{– Eh?!\N– Eh?! - OG}– Huh?!\N– Huh?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.26,0:17:09.22,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{– Leave all the gold behind?!\N– Leave all the gold behind?! - OG}– You want us to leave all the gold?!\N– You want us to leave all the gold?!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.72,0:17:14.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Noland and his men\Nare preparing to leave. - OG}Noland and his men\Nare preparing to set sail.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.61,0:17:27.23,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Mousse! Where were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:30.74,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What if...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:35.20,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What if you knew a single, important tree... - OG}What if you knew that\Na single, precious tree...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.70,0:17:38.16,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{was tainted by poison... - OG}was tainted with a deadly poison...{Polly/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.91,0:17:42.83,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{And that its poison would eventually spread into the forest, - OG}and that this poison would eventually\Nspread throughout the forest,{CB/Z/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:46.30,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{affect people, and kill an island?! - OG}then to its people,\Nkilling the entire island?{CB/Z/Polly/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:49.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What if you knew beforehand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.34,0:17:50.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{What do you mean? - OG}What are you saying?{Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.92,0:17:52.38,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:54.05,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,If it was us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.43,0:17:57.76,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,what would we do...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.56,0:18:01.44,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{with that single, important tree?! - OG}with that single, precious tree?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.56,0:18:06.82,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Dad! Go quickly and stop them! - OG}{Dad! You must go and stop them! - CB}Papa, hurry and stop them!{Z}{Hurry and stop them, papa! - Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.82,0:18:09.69,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Don't be a fool!\NYou know what they've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.69,0:18:13.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{If we part now, we'll regret it for the rest of our lives! - OG}If we leave things like this,\Nwe'll regret it for the rest of our lives!{Z/WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.03,0:18:15.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,You finally made such a dear friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:18.45,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,and we Shandians owe them so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.45,0:18:20.91,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{But we're going to leave them hurt for the rest of their lives! - OG}Let them go, and their pain\Nwill never heal!{CB/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:23.12,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.75,0:18:25.79,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,It'll probably sound like an excuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.38,0:18:30.21,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{but for the commodore's honor, I must say this. - OG}but for the commodore's honor,\NI'll tell you anyway.{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.21,0:18:33.47,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,Those woods of yours\Nwere already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.47,0:18:34.47,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Eh?! - OG}Huh?!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:37.93,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{The true horror of\Nthe Kinetsu plague... - OG}The true horror of a\Ntree fever outbreak...{PP/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.56,0:18:42.39,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{is that it can also infect plant life. - OG}is that it also infects plant life.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:45.23,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,It was because he knew this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:48.98,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{that the commodore pleaded with you without regard for his own life. - OG}that the commodore risked\Nhis own life to plead with you.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:53.15,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{From people to forest, forest to people... - OG}From people to forest,\Nfrom forest to people...{Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.15,0:18:58.41,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{Several small islands have been destroyed in exactly that way. - OG}That is precisely how it\Ndevastates small islands.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.41,0:19:02.79,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing\Nto worry about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:06.71,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,We finished checking\Nthe entire forest yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.71,0:19:09.88,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry that we cut down your beloved woods - OG}I'm sorry, we had no idea\Nthe trees we cut down were precious,{CB/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.88,0:19:11.96,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{without knowing or explaining... - OG}but we still should have explained.{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:16.09,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{It'd probably still be unforgivable even with an explanation, - OG}Well, I don't expect you to forgive us,\Neven with an explanation...{CB/Nikki/Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:20.47,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,but a botanist would never harm\Na forest without good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.93,0:19:24.69,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,{The commodore doesn't hate gods and spirits and stuff... - OG}It's not that the commodore\Nhates gods or spirits...{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:31.86,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,it's just that he always knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.86,0:19:33.61,Flashbacks-207-,,0,0,0,,what's most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:38.87,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,That means... they did it for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:44.96,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Dad! - OG}Papa!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.62,0:19:49.42,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.04,0:19:52.17,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,Don't go yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.05,0:19:54.88,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Everyone have everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.76,0:19:57.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{All except one thing... - OG}Not {\i1}everything{\i0}...{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.34,0:19:59.34,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Quit mopin'! Just forget about it! - OG}Quit mopin'! Forget about it!{CB/Nikki}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:01.43,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{All right! It's time to go! - OG}Alright! It's time to go!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.43,0:20:02.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Everyone to your positions! - OG}Positions, everyone!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.89,0:20:05.81,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{We're now heading back to the Kingdom of Lvneel! - OG}We're heading home to\Nthe Kingdom of Lvneel!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.81,0:20:08.15,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,– Aye, aye!\N– Aye, aye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.15,0:20:10.61,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:13.98,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,{I've committed such a sin! - OG}I've committed a grave sin!{Polly}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:17.57,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,Wait! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:22.24,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.21,0:20:31.50,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.34,0:20:33.92,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,is the bell ringing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.84,0:20:36.80,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Ring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:39.59,Thoughts-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry, Noland - -san}{! - OG}We're sorry, Noland!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:41.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Louder!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.14,0:20:43.14,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{So Noland and the others can hear it! - OG}{So Noland and his crew can hear it! - PP}Make sure Noland's crew can hear it!{WF}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:47.56,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Commodore! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:21:01.03,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.45,0:21:03.24,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Kalgara...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:22.93,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Come back again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:25.89,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Noland...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.89,0:21:29.35,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll be waiting for you here! - OG}I'll be waiting right here for you!{Polly/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.52,0:21:33.56,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll keep on ringing the bell! - OG}I'll keep ringing the bell for you!{Polly/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.98,0:21:38.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,So that your ship won't get\Nlost at sea when you return...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.99,0:21:42.99,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,So that you won't lose sight\Nof this island during a storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.99,0:21:47.33,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{I'll ring this bell and wait for you! - OG}I'll ring the bell and wait for you!{Polly/CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.63,0:22:02.76,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Let's meet again someday for sure! Friend of mine! - OG}Let's make sure to meet again\Nsomeday... my precious friend!{CB/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.22,0:22:06.51,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.22,0:22:09.72,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,come back again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.94,0:22:15.52,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,{Of course I'll be back! - OG}Of course I'll come back!{CB}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.52,0:22:17.07,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.86,0:22:25.66,Main-207-,,0,0,0,,Let's meet again someday for sure!
